post_text: On Friday over 80 LAF orchestra students joined Mr. Keller to kick off his Masterclass Series. Kara Markley Sterling introduced themes in Celtic music and discussed the role of "improvisation". This Friday we are looking forward to Dr. Jennifer Jolley Texas Tech Composition Professor !. The series will round out with Sue On, professional violinist and conductor of the Lakeland Symphony Orchestra, Keegan Lammers, music student Depauw University, and Cooperford CHS Alum and Orchestra Director at North Brunswick Township High School.

post_text: Supervisor Danielle Dagounis and Design and Technology teachers Jessica Liatys and Kyle Kermick are helping front line healthcare workers. They have designed filtration masks using 3D printers and are ready to begin mass production as soon as they get approval from local hospitals. The School District has donated N95 masks and glove sets and will continue to support the medical community where possible.

post_text: Cougar Field will currently remain open to the community. As communicated over the weekend social distancing protocols should still be followed when using the field. As a reminder there are no dogs permitted at the field or on any School District Property. There is a continuing issue with dog waste on the turf at Cougar field, which poses a health risk to anyone who uses it. Dogs also are causing damage to the turf. The School District has made a significant investment in Cougar field and we need you to help us protect this asset if you would like for the field to remain open to the community. We appreciate your understanding and cooperation in respecting the No Dogs Allowed signage and welcome your support in encouraging others to do the same. If there is a continued issue with dog presence and waste the Board of Education will be required to close Cougar field to the public in order to make them safe for students to utilize.

post_text:
We are excited to announce that we will be offering one section of full day kindergarten at MAS, WAS, and SBS. If you are interested in participating in the lottery for full day kindergarten please register by midnight on March 3. Questions may be directed to Sally Moreno at smoreno@chatham-nj.org.

More detailed information about the full day program may be found at: https://www.chatham-nj.org/cms/lib/NJ01000518/Centricity/Domain/756/Full-Day%20Kindergarten%20Announcement.pdf.

You may enter the lottery at: https://www.chatham-nj.org//cms/module/selectsurvey/TakeSurvey.aspx?SurveyID=460

post_text: Great Kindness Challenge underway in Chatham! SDOC Partnering with Bridges Outreach to deliver much needed food to the homeless, Mr. Cronin and Mrs. Worden's 5th Graders at LAF made 150 lunches with encouraging messages. post_text: Kindergarten Registration will take place from January 13- 24, 2020. To schedule an appointment, contact Sally Moreno, District Registrar, at 973-457-2560. Registration will take place at the new Board of Education offices at 259 Lafayette Avenue, Chatham, NJ 07928 behind Chatham High School. Appointments will be scheduled in fifteen-minute increments, so please arrive promptly. You must go to the district website at www.chatham-nj.org and complete the required registration packet, prior to your appointment. Decisions on Full Day Kindergarten will be communicated in February once general registration is complete.
